From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrew Gazelka <andrew.gazelka@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026 12:20:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add fallible_int_fallback lint

Flags silently substituting a fallback value for a failed integer
conversion: .unwrap_or, .unwrap_or_default, and .unwrap_or_else on a
Result<_, TryFromIntError> all hide an overflow the same way. The
message/help spells out that the default masks the overflow and how to
fix it (propagate, explicit clamp, or allow-with-reason). Ships a UI test
covering all three methods plus the try_into() form, with negative cases
(Option::unwrap_or, a non-int-error Result, an explicit min-then-cast).

Squashed here: the original lint only covered unwrap_or/unwrap_or_default;
the unwrap_or_else coverage, sharpened diagnostics, and UI test landed as
a follow-up fixup (was patch 0016) and are folded in so the series has one
patch per lint.

